description: Superstar writer Jeph Loeb (SUPERMAN/BATMAN) and the red-hot art team of Ian Churchill and Norm Rapmund join forces to deliver the adventures of Superman's cousin from Krypton, the one and only Kara Zor-el! Spinning out of the megapopular hit SUPERMAN/BATMAN: SUPERGIRL, this volume collecting SUPERGIRL #0-5 tells the story of Supergirl's whirlwind tour of the DCU! Along the way, she encounters the JSA, the Teen Titans, the Outsiders, and the JLA — but will she be an ally or enemy to the world's heroes?
name: Volume 1

description: The deadly super-spy from IRON MAN 2, INVINCIBLE IRON MAN and CAPTAIN AMERICA in her own ongoing series! Natasha Romanoff is not a super hero. She’s not psychic. She doesn’t fly. And yet as the Black Widow, she manages to hold her own against a world of incredibly powerful enemies…and allies. But now someone has tried to kill Natasha…and almost succeeded. Injured gravely, almost beyond her ability to recover, Black Widow sets out to find her attacker…with no suspects and no leads. Who could be deadly enough to get the drop on Natasha? And what connections do they have to some of her closest super hero friends…? Plus, a backup detailing the deadly history of the Black Widow!
name: The Name of the Rose, Part 1

description: The spotlight falls on Fawcett Comics this issue as MOM reprints examples of five of Fawcett’s finest features. Cover star Commando Yank leads off in a big, 12-page action thriller, “Danger At The Dyke”, from America’s Greatest Comics #7, then it’s 14 pages of Minute Man, as he “Makes The Dictators Buy War Bonds!”, drawn by Phil Bard in his best pseudo-Kirby style. It is also fro AGC #7. Bulletman rings in,with “The Curio Shop Murders”, done by master brushman Bill Ward, from Master Commics #100.Plus, Ibis The Invincible and The Golden Arrow(by Dick Giordano and Vince Alascia). Also, “The Collector’s Corner”, by Bill Black-on The Marvel Families’ last Golden Age appearance. Color cover, interiors are black and white with graytones. 52-page standard comic book format.

Special all Simon and Kirby issue!!! Covered here in great detail are the colorful careers of some of Joe Simon and Jack Kirby’s most awesome creations including Captain 3-D (Featuring a unique standard-comic recreation if the origin of Cap from Captain 3D #1, AND some of the never-before-seen Mort Meskin pencils for the nevedr-published Captain 3D #2.), Bullseye, and the much-celebrated Boy’s Ranch. Each feature covers the subject issue-by-issue and all text is profusely illustrated. Even the cover is a representation of the cover art created for the unpublished Captain 3D #2. A complete Jack Kirby Black Owl story will be featured, exactly as it was seen in Prize Comics #8, in December of 1940, and part one of an actual interview with Joe Simon!! Don’t miss this one!!! Color cover by Kirby and Black, interiors are black and white with graytones. 52-page standard comic book format.

This issue features two double length action stories Fawcett’s Mr. Scarlet and Pinky must solve the mystery of “The Runaway Room”, as drawn by Jack Binder for America’s Greatest Comics #7, in 1943; then it’s Airboy from Hillman Publications in “Monsters From The Ice”, featuring one of his most memorable enemies, Zzed. This story originally appeared in Airboy #76, and is drawn by Ernie Schroeder.Then, it’s “Bulletman Vs. The Torpedo”, with art by Harry Anderson, from Master Comics circa 1945, and two special treats- future Mad creator Harvey Kurtzman tries his hand at a superhero on Buckskin, in “Barn Of The Doomed”, from a 1943 issue of Ace Publications’ Super Mystery Comics, AND a Phantom Lady story that was DRAWN for her mid-50′s Ajax/Farrel run, BUT NEVER BEFORE PRINTED ANYWHERE-”Two Times Zero” This inventory story was left over after the title was cancelled in the ’50′s, and we aquired the original art!! A rare find indeed. Color covers, interiors are black and white with graytones. 52-page standard comic book format.

The “Warsawia”, a boat that is travelling along the Iquitos-Leticia route, is wrecked on the River Amazon. Among the survivors are Mister No, Dona Florida (the madame of a brothel) and Felix her helper, Dr. Adler, a shifty German doctor, as well as a strange monk, Father León, and Corinna Wilke, a mysterious woman …
name: Tempesta sul Rio Amazonas

description: Corinna Wilkes has escaped from Lima with a suitcase full of jewels, after killing her boyfriend, a gangland heavy. El Jefe’s men follow her to recover the jewels. But this is not the only problem for Mister No and the other survivors: an anonymous assassin kills Felix, Dona Florinda’s helper, and not even Father León seems trustworthy…
name: Senza Via di Scampo

description: Salvador de Bahia. In the heart of Brazil, Mister No meets Mestre Zulu, the charismatic master of a Capoeira school, and his attractive pupil Margarida. Zulu is against the “Quilombistas” of the mysterious Zuma, who transform the justifiable rage against the landowners into homicidal madness. And they will soon cross paths with Mister No…
name: Le Notti di Bahia

description: Has Miranda, an old friend of Mister No’s, finally found the man of her dreams? It looks like it. She has married the rich landowner Lincoln Terreiro da Sousa and Jerry accompanies them to Lincoln’s Fazenda. But the “Quilombistas”, the terrorists who are fighting against the big landowners, kidnap her. It is Mister No who goes to free her, entering the rebel’s impregnable lair…
name: I Ribelli del Sertão

description: Mister No is forced into an emergency landing in an unexplored area of the jungle. The region is populated by an unusual tribe, containing white children who speak Spanish. Where do they come from? Within this unusual group the leader Raphael and Lucho, chief of the hunters, are rival contenders for power. It will be Mister No who pays the price…
name: Il Villaggio Nascosto

description: The children found in the jungle came from an orphanage in Bogotá, the “Madre de Jesús”. Lucho’s men kill Raphael, blaming Mister No. Civil War breaks out in the strange community. But Luna, the clairvoyant woman who is a friend of Mister No, has a premonitory dream…
name: Cuore Selvaggio

description: Fogerty, Mister No’s old friend, is a man whose life has turned its back on him. He was a pilot for a company in Patagonia and was fired. Now his only companion is the bottle. But he has a last chance: cooperating with the group of robbers who plan to rob a mining company in Columbia. However fate is against him and against Mister No…
name: Tragica Rapina

description: The brothers Michael and Jordan Crocker have carried out a large robbery, during which their pilot, Fogerty, was killed. The two force Mister No into helping them, but the police, led by Sergeant Ibanez, are after them. What is more, there are others who are after the Crocker brothers as well, others who are interested in the content of the mysterious stolen briefcase….
name: Nelle Mani dei Banditi

description: Finally after twenty years, Professor Jerome Drake is released from the Rykers Island Jail. They attempt to kill him, but an old friend, Domingo Sangrel, saves his life. The two agree to meet in Santiago in Chile, a month later. First, however, the Professor has to go to Manaus, to meet his son Jerry…
name: Vent'Anni Dopo

description: Mister No detests his father because he believes him to be a murderer and because his father abandoned him to go to fight in the Spanish War, just when Jerry needed him most. Jerome Drake tells him what really happened, the real story of how they came into possession of an enormous quantity of gold and how he was betrayed by his best friend…
name: Terra e Libertà

description: The fog of mystery is clearing. Jerome Drake sees the attractive Petra again, the passionate Polish woman with whom he fought in the Spanish War, and he meets many other fellow soldiers from both sides of the barricades. Together once more, they set off in search of the Spanish gold. And Mister No and Esse-Esse are also with them!
name: Il Traditore

description: Whisky Manaus. Only a few days to the year 2000, but certain things never change. Even at his age Mister No still likes drinking, courting women and engaging in fist fights. He is still brave and strong, like Esse-Esse, who is still his best friend. However, Jerry receives an unexpected visit: it is James, Phil Mulligan’s son, who wants to become…the new Mister No!
name: L'Ultima Frontiera
Lust For Power

description: EXTRA PAGES!! MORE NEW “RETRO” STORIES!!! A comics event!! Six actual Golden Age heroes, revived in the AC universe as supporting characters in the monumental Shroud War storyline in the Femforce monthly, each in their own solo saga, in action on there own for the first time since the 1940′s!!! And, although these tales carefully crafted by contemporay creators, the stories are all set back in the hero’s original time period’s, between 1940 and 1950. See Harry “A” Chesler Publication’s Black Cobra, (From Dynamic Comics and Captain Flight) in “Reptiles Of The Madman”, written by Mark Heike, and drawn by Brad (Spawn) Gorby; Fox Features’ U. S. Jones (From Wonderworld Comics, and his own title.) in “The Secret Of The Deathhawk”, with script and layouts by Mark Heike, and finishes by Stephanie ( Big Bang ) Sanderson; Holyoke/Continental’s Black Venus, (From Contact Comics )in “Ghost Of The Scarlet Salamander”, written abd drawn by Mark Heike; Nedor/Standard’s Pyroman, ( From Startling and America’s Best Comics. )in “Mystery Of The Space Kittens”, script, layouts and inks by Mark Heike, and pencils by Eric Coile; Prize Comic’s The Black Owl in “The Fangs Of The Flying Fox”, written by Mark Heike, and drawn by Bill Black, and Fox Feature’s The Flame and Flame Girl, (From Wonderworld, Big Three, and his own title.) in “Slaves Of The Lotus Demon”, script and breakdowns by Mark Heike, finished artwork by Tony Manginelli. And, just to make sure these guys got it right, there’s an actual vintage G. A. reprint story, Fox Feature’s The Green Mask in “Horror Sings A Song”, from Green Mask #9, with art by Louis and Arturo Cazeneuve, and Pierce Rice. Color painted cover by Brad Gorby, interiors are black and white. 52 pages, 67/8″ X 8″ Retro comic size.

In 1937 the city of Shanghai was a haven for a shady criminal underworld.

Detective Harry Lo was on the trail of Kobi, the master smuggler who had killed Harry's best friend.

Then the brutal Japanese Army invaded China and Harry was forced to stand alongside his sworn enemy. If they did not work together they would never survive the deadly streets of Shanghai.
name: Streets of Shanghai
Gatto Silvestro e la Lezione di Caccia
L'Atlante delle Regioni d'Italia: la Calabria
Bugs Bunny Meets the Dwarf Ghost

description: Siege: Loki, from Kieron Gillen and Jamie McKelvie, goes deep into the mind of Siege’s most devious major player!
name: Loki

description:
After a disastrous RAF raid on a V-1 factory, Luftwaffe investigators moved in. Soon all the Lancaster bombers that the German anti-aircraft gunners and night-fighter crews had claimed to have shot down were accounted for. All that is, but one.

Hauptmann Wilhelm Furth, in charge of the investigation, wasn't worried. After all, a 21-metre-long Lancaster couldn't be hard to find... could it?
name: The Lost Bomber

description: In Siege: Captain America, from Christos Gage and Federico Dallocchio, learn more about the role of Bucky Barnes and Steve Rogers in this war and how it will define their relationship!
name: Bear Any Burden

description: In Siege: Young Avengers, from Sean McKeever and Mahmud A. Asrar, the Young Avengers take center stage as Wiccan and Patriot are pushed to their limits!
name: Underneath It All

volume.name: Friendly Ghost Casper and the Friendly Dentist

description:
1. Tone-Deaf
 
2. Funny Man
 
3. Sick Leave
 
4. Phony Baloney
 
5. Boners, Moaners and Groaners (text jokes)
 
6. Travel Trouble
name: Tone-Deaf

description: A DAME TO GET KILLED FOR. When a widow hires Deadpool to avenge her husband and kill The Punisher, Wade Wilson follows a trail that leads him under the city of NY and headfirst into an army of monsters lead by the animated remains of his prey. What he finds is that FrankenCastle is already dead... but that doesn't make him any less deadly.
name: A Dame To Get Killed For

description:
1. Warts so Horrible? (hosted by The Old Witch / written by Albert B. Feldstein : reprinted from: Haunt of Fear (EC, 1950) #9)
 
2. Forbidden Fruit (hosted by The Vault Keeper / written by Albert B. Feldstein : reprinted from: Haunt of Fear (EC, 1950) #9)  
 
3. The Age-Old Story (hosted by The Old Witch / written by Albert B. Feldstein : reprinted from: Haunt of Fear (EC, 1950) #9) 
 
4. The Gorilla's Paw (hosted by The Crypt Keeper / written by Albert B. Feldstein : reprinted from: Haunt of Fear (EC, 1950) #9)
name: Warts so Horrible?

description: Kraven the Hunter. Even in death, his legacy has managed to torture The Amazing Spider-Man. As the effects of the Gauntlet rage around Spider-Man, Kraven’s family have been pulling the strings towards a mysterious and sinister end game. This month, Fred Van Lente & Barry Kitson bring you the brutal training days of a young Sergei Kravinoff. See how the man became the hunter…and why a family needs his leadership more than ever. Meanwhile in the Spectacular Spider-Girl, the gang war heats up and a last page reveal that will rock Mayday Parker’s world as SOMEONE’s coming to town…and a lifelong war on crime is rekindled. And last year, the density-altering Paper Doll sliced into Spidey’s life as she stalked celebrity Bobby Carr, then boyfriend of Mary Jane Watson. Now that MJ’s back in New York…and Bobby Carr’s life has taken a huge tumble…you better believe she’s gunning for the Redhead. Can Spidey save her in time? Find out as Joe Casey and Jim Mahfood stop by to bring you PAPER CUTS!
name: Gauntlet Origins: Kraven; Here Comes Wild Card; Fashion Spread

description: The remains of Gen 13 wander a post-apocalyptic America struggling not only to stay together as a team, but to simply survive. Unfortunately, an army of robotic zealots intent on wiping the remains of humanity off the face of the Earth has other ideas. Plus, who is The Pathcutter?
name: Pocatello, Part 1: Pathcutter

description: One of America's genuine cartoon classics, Felix the Cat has delighted and entertained audiences for over eighty years, reaching nearly every corner of the globe in newspaper strips, animated cartoons, toys, games, and comic books, becoming so famous that Felix was chosen as Charles Lindbergh's mascot for his landmark transatlantic flight as well as being the very first image broadcast over television airwaves! And now, with Felix still appearing in everything from animated cartoons to video games to music CDs, Dark Horse adds Felix the Cat's Greatest Hits to the playlist, presenting a selection of stories featuring Felix, his friends and foes, and, of course, his Magic Bag of Tricks! Felix the Cat's Greatest Hits is nonstop fun and laughs for comics readers of all ages. As a special addition, this book features Pin-Ups by Mort Walker, Chris Browne and Art Clokey!

War of the Iron Men, Part One

The Armored Avenger’s second on-going series kicks off with a bang as the WAR OF THE IRON MEN begins here! Tony Stark’s worst fears are realized when stolen Iron Man technology is used for ethnic cleansing in a civil war-ravaged land. When he defies U.S. government orders to confront the armored assassins himself, Stark sets off an international conflagration that threatens his friends, his company, and his very life -- and sets him on a collision course with China and Russia, and their champions, Radioactive Man, Titanium Man and the Crimson Dynamo! Guest-stars galore! And a shocking last page reveal of the classic Shell-head villain behind it all you won’t want to miss!

"Iron Man is Born!"

A reprint of the comic Tales of Suspense #39.
name: War of the Iron Men, Part One

description:
'INTERNATIONAL FLAVOR,' Conclusion

Cannibal vs. bloodsucker.
name: International Flavor, Part 5

description: Nara's old nemesis Violet returns and she wants revenge. But when the truth about Violet's resurrection is revealed, Nara must confront an ugly secret within the Zodiac. Meanwhile, Asia finds herself captive of the terrible Witch Queen.

“TIFFANY BLUES,” Part Four: “WHY WOULD ANYONE CARE ABOUT ANOTHER DREAM?”
The battle between the Baron and the Toymaker escalates as armies of toys are built to do battle. But as war heats up, Tiffany, the subject of their fallout faces a nightmare of her own.
name: Part 4 of 5: Tiffany Blues

description: "Adopted from the popular radio program"
name: Gang Busters

description: Normally, Forgetless is about the last great club night in New York, and the murderous models that it make so special. But this month, we're doing a story about a sex-addicted koala instead. And trust us, it's even weirder than it sounds. Don't miss the issue EVERYONE will be talking about, if only so they can feel clean again!
name: Rememberful?_04

description:
"LOVE, LIFE, LOST... FOUND"
A night out on the town might not be what Paul expects. But before he can get a handle on what’s really going on -- the evening is interrupted by VIOLENCE and BLOODSHED. Paul watches helplessly as life slips away… R.I.P.
Reprints newspaper strips.
name: Terry and the Pirates

description: The Man of Bronze in his own series at last! Doc Savage is the target of a brazen attack on New York City! Tragedy will strike one of Doc's compatriots, and someone may not survive the opening pages of "The Lord of Lightning!" Written by Paul Malmont, national best-selling author of The Chinatown Death-Cloud Peril, with art by Howard Porter (JLA)! And don't miss the hard-hitting JUSTICE, INC. co-feature, starring Richard Benson, the Avenger! When criminals abduct one of his own detectives, Benson's icy heart sears with a rage hotter than any he's ever known. "Worst Nightmare" begins here, written by crime novelist Jason Starr (THE CHILL) with art by Scott Hampton (LUCIFER)!
name: The Lord of Lightning: Darkness Falls; Worst Nightmare, Part One: The Wounded

description: The new series from the writer of OLYMPUS and the artist of THE SURROGATES. In Oregon, a mysterious virus infects anyone that looks into an electric light. An abusive father blindfolds his daughter and together they escape town as people are burning alive from the inside out. A fierce, action-packed and gritty tale of survival, THE LIGHT is 28 DAYS LATER meets 30 DAYS OF NIGHT.
name: Outbreak

description: As the druids prepare for their ceremony which King Icarus believes will elevate him to godhood, all paths converge on the capital city of Dealrach Ard-Vale. As Karic launches his audacious plan to confront his destiny, Cassius is reunited with his own squad of loyal Templar. Leito strikes an unexpected alliance. And Mornae comes face-to-face with the horrific Snake god!
name: Feast of Samhain

volume.name: The Mice Templar, Volume II: Destiny

description: Halcyon is a savage, unpredictable, brutal place. For some, it's just another backwater world colonized and exploited for its resources. For others, it's home. For decades the settlers of this aberrant moon have lived and worked like slaves, but now a new generation has decided that it's time for independence. Amidst this struggle, cadet Nika McKay returns to his home colony after a decade on Earth in order to search for his true identity. What he finds instead is a young nation on the verge of a civil war.
name: Hellcyon

description: Former Jedi Dass Jennir has woven a tangled web of lies in his quest to topple two opposing gangs. Now, all the threads are about to break, and the gangs will tear the town apart in a war that may doom those Jennir sought to save -- but not before they take their vengeance out on him!
name: Blue Harvest, Part 4
